      </h5>
      <br />
      <h3><b>Description</b></h3>
      <br />
      <p style="font-size: larger; width: 80%">
        <i>
          California rolls are a staple in sushi restaurants and a great
          introduction to sushi for those who may be hesitant about raw fish.
          With a combination of creamy avocado, crisp cucumber, and imitation
          crab meat, these rolls offer a delightful blend of textures and
          flavors. Perfect for a sushi night at home, these rolls are easy to
          make and fun to customize.
        </i>
      </p>
      <hr id="hr" />
      <br /><br />
      <h3><b>Ingredients:</b></h3>
      <br />
      <ul style="font-size: larger">
        <li>2 cups sushi rice</li>
        <li>3 cups water</li>
        <li>1/4 cup rice vinegar</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon sugar</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
        <li>4 sheets of nori (seaweed)</li>
        <li>8 oz imitation crab meat, shredded</li>
        <li>1 avocado, sliced</li>
        <li>1 cucumber, cut into thin strips</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons mayonnaise</li>
        <li>Sesame seeds for garnish</li>
        <li>Soy sauce, pickled ginger, and wasabi for serving</li>
      </ul>
      <hr id="hr" />
      <br /><br />
      <h3><b>Instructions</b></h3>
      <br />
      <ul style="font-size: larger; width: 80%">
        <li>
          <b>Prepare the Sushi Rice:</b> Rinse the sushi rice in cold water
          until the water runs clear. Combine the rice and water in a medium
          saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer
          for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let it sit covered for another 10
          minutes. Transfer the rice to a large bowl.
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
          <b>Season the Rice:</b> In a small bowl, mix the rice vinegar, sugar,
          and salt. Gently fold this mixture into the rice using a wooden spoon
          or spatula. Allow the rice to cool to room temperature.
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
          <b>Assemble the Sushi Rolls:</b> Place a bamboo sushi mat on a flat
          surface and lay a sheet of nori on top. Spread a thin layer of sushi
          rice over the nori, leaving about 1 inch at the top edge.
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
          <b>Add Fillings:</b> Arrange a strip of cucumber, avocado, and a layer
          of shredded imitation crab meat along the edge of the rice, about 1
          inch from the bottom edge of the nori. Spread a small amount of
          mayonnaise over the fillings.
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
          <b>Garnish and Serve:</b> Sprinkle the sushi rolls with sesame seeds.
          Arrange them on a platter and serve with soy sauce, pickled ginger,
          and wasabi on the side.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <br />
      <p style="font-size: larger; width: 80%">
        <b>Enjoy your California rolls!</b> 
        Experiment with different ingredients and sauces to find your perfect
        combination. Happy cooking!
      </p>
